cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.SE 

This paper is about network verification, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the challenges of handling context-dependent policies and stateful network functions, which are related to security (cs.CR) and systems (cs.SY). The paper proposes a practical representation of complex NFs, which involves finite state machines, and uses symbolic execution to tackle state space explosion, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
